s\nin the large-N limit are found variationally. The simplest variational ansatz\nis an analogue of mean-field theory and compares well with exact and numerical\nsolutions of 1 and 2 matrix models away from phase transitions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 27 Sep 2004 19:57:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2007-05-23"}
